    },
    {
      "id": "I0-bJZUBeQi-aLQfe7F3",
      "title": "Griped",
      "color": "#307EE3",
      "tag": "The Writer",
      "snippet": "— What key? Six sharps? / — F sharp major, Ben Dollard said. / Bob Cowley&#x27;s outstretched talons griped the black deepsounding chords.",
      "order": 91,
      "url": "https://www.joyceproject.com/notes/I0-bJZUBeQi-aLQfe7F3"
    },
    {
      "id": "e0-bJZUBeQi-aLQff7Jj",
      "title": "Shah of Persia",
      "color": "#40B324",
      "tag": "Ireland",
      "snippet": "Tuning up. Shah of Persia liked that best. Remind him of home sweet home. Wiped his nose in curtain too. Custom his country perhaps. / Just a question of custom shah of Persia.",
      "order": 92,
      "url": "https://www.joyceproject.com/notes/e0-bJZUBeQi-aLQff7Jj"
    },
    {
